Automated Flight Following (AFF)
description: AFF is GPS-based computer software first developed in 2000. Using a map-based interface, an authorized user can identify, view, and monitor the location of government-registered aircraft, in the air or on the ground. AFF can automatically track specially equipped aircraft, providing location and velocity information in near-real-time to dispatchers and aviation personnel.
